            "content": [
              {
                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "I tried to retrieve sales records from your Fabric workspace but the required data source isn’t available: “I'm unable to provide information about sales records because the required data source is not available. If you have a different question or need information from another topic, please let me know!”.\n\nI can still help — below is a concise overview of sales records and how to work with them, plus next steps to get me the data or run queries.\n\nWhat “sales records” are\n- A persistent log of transactions where goods or services are sold. They form the source of truth for revenue, invoicing, returns, commissions and analytics.\n\nCommon fields you’ll find\n- Transaction ID / Order number\n- Date/time\n- Customer identifier (name, customer ID)\n- Product/SKU, description\n- Quantity, unit price, discount\n- Taxes, shipping, total amount\n- Payment method/status\n- Sales channel (online, in-store, partner)\n- Sales rep / territory\n- Order/invoice status (completed, refunded, returned)\n- Timestamps for creation/updates, and audit trail metadata\n\nTypical formats & storage\n- Relational tables (OLTP systems, data warehouse)\n- CSV / Excel exports\n- JSON from APIs (e-commerce platforms)\n- ERP/CRM systems (e.g., SAP, Netsuite, Salesforce)\n\nCommon uses and analyses\n- Revenue and trend reports (daily/weekly/monthly)\n- Average order value (AOV), units per order\n- Customer lifetime value (LTV), churn, cohort analysis\n- Conversion funnels and sales velocity\n- Inventory forecasting and stock replenishment\n- Commission and payroll calculations\n- Fraud detection and exception reporting\n\nBest practices\n- Single source of truth (unique IDs, canonical customer/product dimensions)\n- Record returns and refunds as linked transactions, not negative aggregates\n- Capture timestamps and user/process that changed records (audit log)\n- Validate data on entry (required fields, types, ranges)\n- Retention/archival policy and backups\n- Secure PII and payment data; follow PCI-DSS and relevant privacy laws\n\nHow I can help next\n- If you want me to fetch or analyze your actual sales records, you can:\n  - Grant the Fabric workspace access to the data source, or\n  - Upload a sample CSV/Excel here, or\n  - Tell me the platform (Shopify, Stripe, Salesforce, database) and what report or metric you need.\n- I can also help design a schema, write queries, build dashboards, or suggest KPIs.\n\nWhat would you like to do next — analyze a specific dataset, get a report, or fix an issue with your sales records?",
